text.section:
A member qualifies for a pension under subsection (b) of this section if the member:
is an elected or appointed official of the State at the time of application for retirement; and
was initially an elected or appointed official of the State before July 22, 1981;
is an elected or appointed official of the State when separating from employment;
was initially an elected or appointed official of the State during the period from July 22, 1981, through June 30, 1982, both inclusive; and
separated from employment involuntarily as certified by the Secretary of Budget and Management;
was promoted to a position in the unclassified service of the State on or before June 30, 1982;
has been in the unclassified service or its equivalent in the State continuously from June 30, 1982, until separating from employment; and
separated from employment involuntarily as certified by the Secretary of Budget and Management; or
is a deputy clerk of the court at the time of application for retirement; and
was initially a deputy clerk of the court before July 22, 1981.

section.section:
On the appointment or election of a retiree described in paragraph (1) of this subsection:
the retiree's retirement allowance shall stop;
the retiree may rejoin the Employees' Retirement System;
the retiree shall make member contributions at the same rate the retiree paid before retirement; and
the Board of Trustees shall restore any creditable service or eligibility service to the retiree's credit at the time of retirement.
